a2c23396  //
9cfb3c79  // emitEvent's signature is signature-stable from the Phase 2 Wave-0 stub
5ba33cb6  // (Phase 2 D-01: "empty telemetry stub now > telemetry-retrofit-workspace
cb55f11c  // later"). Every existing call site in @emmy/provider, @emmy/tools, and
1b86a657  // @emmy/ux keeps compiling unchanged.
a2c23396  //
995e6d65  // Dual-sink contract (RESEARCH §Pattern 3):
cf2c0fb8  //   - JSONL authoritative (appendJsonlAtomic; for records > PIPE_BUF fall
91a2e1d5  //     back to writeJsonAtomic tempfile+rename shape per Pattern A risk note).
1a5a7458  //     JSONL write never propagates fs errors upward — logs to stderr and
3665636a  //     continues so the agent loop is not blocked on disk IO.
28a375d3  //   - OTLP best-effort (tracer.startSpan + setAttribute + end). OTLP failure
f1d738e5  //     never propagates; JSONL remains authoritative. Exceptions during the
ba0621af  //     tracer path are swallowed per D-06.
a2c23396  //
b65ce910  // Profile stamp semantics:
2f6059ef  //   Every record's top-level `profile` key (if present) is flattened into
a9dd8463  //   emmy.profile.* span attributes AT emitEvent time. Additionally, the
f4af7845  //   EmmyProfileStampProcessor installed in otel-sdk.ts auto-stamps those
9b7aa630  //   same attrs on EVERY span started via the global Tracer (including spans
593c77e0  //   created by downstream code paths that do not go through emitEvent). The
e5623822  //   two mechanisms are redundant by design — per-event stamping keeps the
39d4e78f  //   JSONL record self-describing; processor stamping catches spans created
916a21a6  //   outside the emitEvent path (e.g. HARNESS-09 chat spans in Plan 03-03).
e3b0c442  
